<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Preparatory_signal">Preparatory signal</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Racing_Rules_of_Sailing&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Preparatory signal"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>These signal flags are used before a race start and most commonly as part of a start sequence/procedure.
</p>
<table class="wikitable">

<tbody><tr style="text-align: center; font-weight: bold;">
<td colspan="2" width="120px">Flag signal</td>
<td width="100px">Number of sound signals when raised</td>
<td width="100px">Number of sound signals when lowered</td>
<td width="500px">Description
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td width="90px"><figure class="mw-halign-center mw-image-border" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:ICS_Papa.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d0/ICS_Papa.svg/50px-ICS_Papa.svg.png" decoding="async" width="50" height="50" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d0/ICS_Papa.svg/75px-ICS_Papa.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d0/ICS_Papa.svg/100px-ICS_Papa.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="600" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td width="30px" align="center"><b>P</b>
</td>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Speaker_Icon.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/20px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png" decoding="async" width="20" height="20" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/30px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/40px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Speaker_Icon.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/20px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png" decoding="async" width="20" height="20" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/30px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/40px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td>Normal preparatory signal - no starting penalties are in effect. A boat over the line at the start can return through the line or round an end but must keep clear of boats not returning. If they fail to return through the line however they will be scored <a href="/wiki/On_course_side" title="On course side">OCS (on course side)</a>.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center mw-image-border" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:ICS_India.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/ICS_India.svg/50px-ICS_India.svg.png" decoding="async" width="50" height="50" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/ICS_India.svg/75px-ICS_India.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/ICS_India.svg/100px-ICS_India.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="600" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td align="center"><b>I</b>
</td>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Speaker_Icon.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/20px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png" decoding="async" width="20" height="20" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/30px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/40px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Speaker_Icon.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/20px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png" decoding="async" width="20" height="20" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/30px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/40px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td>The Round-an-End Rule 30.1 will be in effect. A boat over the line during the minute before the start must sail to the pre-start side of the line around either end before starting. If they fail to do this they will be scored <a href="/wiki/On_course_side" title="On course side">OCS</a>.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center mw-image-border" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:ICS_Zulu.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c6/ICS_Zulu.svg/50px-ICS_Zulu.svg.png" decoding="async" width="50" height="50" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c6/ICS_Zulu.svg/75px-ICS_Zulu.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c6/ICS_Zulu.svg/100px-ICS_Zulu.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="600" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td align="center"><b>Z</b>
</td>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Speaker_Icon.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/20px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png" decoding="async" width="20" height="20" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/30px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/40px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Speaker_Icon.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/20px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png" decoding="async" width="20" height="20" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/30px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/40px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td>The 20% Penalty Rule 30.2 will be in effect. A boat within the triangle formed by the ends of the line and the first mark during the minute before the start will receive a 20% scoring penalty.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center mw-image-border" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:ICS_India.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/ICS_India.svg/50px-ICS_India.svg.png" decoding="async" width="50" height="50" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/ICS_India.svg/75px-ICS_India.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/ICS_India.svg/100px-ICS_India.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="600" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure> <figure class="mw-halign-center mw-image-border" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:ICS_Zulu.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c6/ICS_Zulu.svg/50px-ICS_Zulu.svg.png" decoding="async" width="50" height="50" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c6/ICS_Zulu.svg/75px-ICS_Zulu.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c6/ICS_Zulu.svg/100px-ICS_Zulu.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="600" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td align="center"><b>I</b><br /><b>Z</b>
</td>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Speaker_Icon.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/20px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png" decoding="async" width="20" height="20" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/30px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/40px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Speaker_Icon.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/20px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png" decoding="async" width="20" height="20" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/30px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/40px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td>Both the I flag rule and the <a href="/wiki/Z_flag" title="Z flag">Z flag</a> Rule will be in effect during the minute before the start. If they fail to round an end then they will be scored <a href="/wiki/On_course_side" title="On course side">OCS</a>.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Auto_Racing_Black.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Auto_Racing_Black.svg/50px-Auto_Racing_Black.svg.png" decoding="async" width="50" height="38" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Auto_Racing_Black.svg/75px-Auto_Racing_Black.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Auto_Racing_Black.svg/100px-Auto_Racing_Black.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="512" data-file-height="384" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td>
</td>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Speaker_Icon.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/20px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png" decoding="async" width="20" height="20" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/30px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/40px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Speaker_Icon.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/20px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png" decoding="async" width="20" height="20" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/30px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/40px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td>The Black Flag Rule 30.3 will be in effect. A boat within the triangle formed by the ends of the line and the first mark during the minute before the start will be disqualified without a hearing. (Renumbered to 30.4 in the 2017–2020 edition.)
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center mw-image-border" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:ICS_Uniform.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/ICS_Uniform.svg/50px-ICS_Uniform.svg.png" decoding="async" width="50" height="50" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/ICS_Uniform.svg/75px-ICS_Uniform.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/ICS_Uniform.svg/100px-ICS_Uniform.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="600" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td align="center"><b>U</b>
</td>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Speaker_Icon.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/20px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png" decoding="async" width="20" height="20" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/30px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/40px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td><figure class="mw-halign-center" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Speaker_Icon.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/20px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png" decoding="async" width="20" height="20" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/30px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/40px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
</td>
<td>The U Flag Rule will be in effect. A boat within the triangle formed by the ends of the line and the first mark during the minute before the start will be disqualified without a hearing. If a restart or resail is called, the disqualification is rescinded, unlike the black-flag or Z-flag penalties. (Added to the 2017–2020 edition as rule 30.3; already frequently included in sailing instructions for specific regattas.)
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Start_signal">Start signal</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Racing_Rules_of_Sailing&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Start signal"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>These signal flags are used in the pre-start procedure.  Class flags can be numeral pennants 1 <span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:ICS_Pennant_One.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c1/ICS_Pennant_One.svg/50px-ICS_Pennant_One.svg.png" decoding="async" width="50" height="28" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c1/ICS_Pennant_One.svg/75px-ICS_Pennant_One.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c1/ICS_Pennant_One.svg/100px-ICS_Pennant_One.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="540" data-file-height="300" /></a></span>, 2 <span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:ICS_Pennant_Two.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c0/ICS_Pennant_Two.svg/50px-ICS_Pennant_Two.svg.png" decoding="async" width="50" height="28" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c0/ICS_Pennant_Two.svg/75px-ICS_Pennant_Two.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c0/ICS_Pennant_Two.svg/100px-ICS_Pennant_Two.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="540" data-file-height="300" /></a></span>, and 3 <span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:ICS_Pennant_Three.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/64/ICS_Pennant_Three.svg/50px-ICS_Pennant_Three.svg.png" decoding="async" width="50" height="28" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/64/ICS_Pennant_Three.svg/75px-ICS_Pennant_Three.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/64/ICS_Pennant_Three.svg/100px-ICS_Pennant_Three.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="540" data-file-height="300" /></a></span> however they can be substituted to avoid confusion with the postponement signals relating to a particular class.
</p>
